Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:18.49,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much for towing our car.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.49,0:00:21.42,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,The mechanic will have an \Neasier time finding your car
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.41,0:00:24.87,Ryohei,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Saeki Ryohei (24) \NGoto Research Lab Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.42,0:00:25.51,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}at the station up ahead than \Nin the middle of the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.87,0:00:30.12,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,We were planning on stopping there \Nto pick up groceries anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.12,0:00:34.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys going camping?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.17,0:00:37.59,Takahiro,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Komada Takahiro (22) \NGoto Research Lab Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.40,0:00:37.89,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Our college lab always \Ngoes camping together.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.10,0:00:40.93,Shoji,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Goto Shoji (50) \NCollege Professor
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.45,0:00:40.92,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Our professor enjoys this kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.92,0:00:42.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.36,0:00:48.82,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Komada-kun, you should get \Na smartphone already.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:48.90,Haruka,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Inoue Haruka (23) \NGoto Research Lab Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.82,0:00:52.17,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,I will once this one breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.17,0:00:56.09,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,It takes too long to exchange data with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.09,0:00:58.04,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Try putting yourself in our shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.04,0:00:59.70,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.70,0:01:01.13,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.13,0:01:05.33,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,This time we're also celebrating the \Npublication of our professor's paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.33,0:01:07.07,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really? That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.52,0:01:12.69,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,The world must be ending if that perverted \Ndrunkard is being recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.69,0:01:15.26,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,H-Haruka-san, he'll hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.26,0:01:18.79,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,He won't wake up. He always gets \Nlike this when he's drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.79,0:01:22.47,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, it's not like you guys \Nlike the professor either.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.47,0:01:24.82,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.82,0:01:27.24,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you all actually think,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.61,0:01:31.38,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,"If only the professor would \Ndisappear from this world."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.81,0:01:43.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Time is the y-axis, and I'm the x-axis!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.02,0:01:45.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Inscribing love and cases \Nwith deductive reasoning!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.11,0:01:46.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The conversation inside the \Ncar is rather ominous!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.94,0:01:48.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I hope nothing happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.13,0:01:50.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.71,0:01:52.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.50,0:01:54.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.98,0:03:41.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(402,1)}The Murderous Carpool
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.04,0:03:39.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Murderous Carpool!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.86,0:03:45.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.28,0:03:52.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. These are for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.32,0:03:54.88,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you didn't need to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:57.76,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to thank you for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.19,0:04:00.28,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where's your friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.28,0:04:03.26,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Saeki-kun? He's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.06,0:04:13.11,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we're leaving soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.11,0:04:14.77,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,We should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.77,0:04:16.28,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.28,0:04:18.57,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.57,0:04:21.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.40,0:04:22.86,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.86,0:04:25.41,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, I'm putting some bags in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.41,0:04:27.23,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.23,0:04:29.33,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking about \Nbringing the car around—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.33,0:04:30.02,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.81,0:04:35.72,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.59,0:04:41.09,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! His phone's stuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.25,0:04:47.02,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.02,0:04:49.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.19,0:04:51.45,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,His phone was stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.45,0:04:52.92,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,The strap was caught on his neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.65,0:04:56.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.32,0:04:59.06,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.06,0:05:01.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:03.44,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,G-Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.44,0:05:06.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone else, please get out of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.70,0:05:09.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch anything at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.59,0:05:19.93,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's wet...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.22,0:05:28.22,Police,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Metropolitan Police Department
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.69,0:05:36.89,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So after you returned from shopping \Nat this store you always stop at,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.89,0:05:40.22,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Goto-san, who had been sleeping inside \Nthe car, slid down in his seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.22,0:05:44.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,causing his phone strap to strangle \Nhim, resulting in his death?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.10,0:05:45.94,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.94,0:05:51.44,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Komada-san, you were the last \Nperson to get out of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.44,0:05:52.24,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.64,0:05:57.24,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,While getting out of the car, I thought \Nthe air inside was a little cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.59,0:06:00.26,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,so I draped a blanket over the professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.62,0:06:03.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you notice anything then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.82,0:06:05.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Anything out of the ordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.90,0:06:12.89,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I didn't recognize \Nthe air cushion the professor was using.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.72,0:06:18.75,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd hurt his back recently, \Nso maybe he bought it for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.18,0:06:25.73,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Inoue-san, you returned to the \Ncar before entering the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.73,0:06:29.90,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I forgot my phone, \Nso I went to go get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.90,0:06:31.94,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,But the professor was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.94,0:06:33.65,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,He was snoring loudly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.03,0:06:37.66,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I went inside and \Ngot a good look at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.12,0:06:40.57,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.57,0:06:42.12,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.12,0:06:43.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.34,0:06:45.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You were with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.18,0:06:49.52,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I dropped my wallet inside the van,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.52,0:06:52.34,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,so I followed Inoue-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.67,0:06:56.86,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,My wallet was on the seat, \Nso I left immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.43,0:07:00.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,but I did hear some loud snoring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.35,0:07:04.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, he fell \Nfrom his seat after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.24,0:07:09.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, Saeki-san, you went to \Nthe convenience store next door
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.11,0:07:12.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,to buy cigarettes after \Nyou finished shopping?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.12,0:07:14.74,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'd just run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.74,0:07:19.03,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,I returned to the car after \Nhaving a smoke over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.03,0:07:23.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We saw him smoking \Ncigarettes. Right, Ran-neechan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.94,0:07:28.54,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. From right around here, \Nwhen we gave them our gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.54,0:07:32.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, did Goto-san \Nalways drink that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.55,0:07:35.86,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Every time he'd be plastered \Nby the time we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.86,0:07:38.57,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,He said he couldn't sleep unless he drank.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.22,0:07:42.71,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,The professor took sleeping pills,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.71,0:07:44.56,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,but he was a shallow sleeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.56,0:07:47.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Alcohol and sleeping pills, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.10,0:07:51.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why there aren't any signs of a \Nstruggle even though he was strangled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.07,0:07:56.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, it seems strange to me \Nthat Goto-san's phone was found
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.08,0:08:02.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,open between the seat and headrest \Nwhen the body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.16,0:08:05.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Goto-san was probably making a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.40,0:08:06.47,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A call?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.47,0:08:10.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible the drunk Goto-san \Ntried to place a call,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.28,0:08:16.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but his hand slipped,\Nand his phone ended up in that gap.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.28,0:08:19.48,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.11,0:08:22.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know something about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.50,0:08:27.47,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,I got a call from the professor \Nwhile I was shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.47,0:08:31.10,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he wanted me to get something,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.48,0:08:30.48,Call,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Incoming Call \NGoto Shoji
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.10,0:08:34.11,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,but he didn't answer, so I hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.53,0:08:35.99,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,11/17 Goto Shoji
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.99,0:08:38.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.13,0:08:43.91,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-kun, investigate Goto-san's \Ncall history immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.91,0:08:44.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.42,0:08:47.75,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,He got what was coming to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.75,0:08:50.12,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Haruka, behave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.12,0:08:53.35,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Saeki-kun, but aren't you relieved?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.12,0:08:57.87,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Now that the professor who refused \Nto give you credits is gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.87,0:09:01.11,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,you'll get that job you were promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.11,0:09:03.50,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,That has nothing to do with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.50,0:09:07.46,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,And, Komada-kun, the professor was \Nawfully verbally abusive towards you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.46,0:09:09.42,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,How did you really feel about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.42,0:09:10.87,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way in particular...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.87,0:09:15.33,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you complained that you wouldn't \Nforgive the professor for sexually harassing you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.33,0:09:18.70,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. That's why I feel relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.70,0:09:20.55,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,You must feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.55,0:09:23.63,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember what he \Nsaid last time he was drunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.06,0:09:25.46,DCItalic,GOTO,0000,0000,0000,,Listen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.46,0:09:30.62,DCItalic,GOTO,0000,0000,0000,,You idiots should shut up and listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.94,0:09:35.37,DCItalic,GOTO,0000,0000,0000,,I can change your futures \Nwith a single word.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.37,0:09:37.15,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.15,0:09:39.38,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I couldn't take it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.38,0:09:40.99,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.37,0:09:50.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like all three of them felt \Nquite resentful towards the professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.66,0:09:54.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need to investigate carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.18,0:09:56.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.45,0:09:58.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Takagi-kun. How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.45,0:10:04.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We found a call placed to Saeki-san \Nin Goto-san's phone history.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.10,0:10:07.39,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We're certain it was during \Nthe time he was shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.39,0:10:08.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.45,0:10:13.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun, did anyone approach \Nthe car while you were here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.85,0:10:17.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No. I was next to the car the \Nwhole time since I was waiting
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.26,0:10:20.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,for the roadside assistance, \Nbut I didn't see anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.60,0:10:25.09,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,If Goto-san died after placing the call,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.09,0:10:29.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and no one approached the car after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.11,0:10:31.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then it must've been an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.31,0:10:33.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.59,0:10:36.15,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,C-C-Conan-kun, you shouldn't be in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.15,0:10:37.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.92,0:10:41.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I dropped something inside the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.88,0:10:45.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. You're always \Nbarging into crime scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.00,0:10:48.90,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, so, what's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.90,0:10:52.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The air cushion Goto-san was using.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.68,0:10:53.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.89,0:10:57.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's so strange about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.18,0:11:02.39,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They said he may have bought \Nit because he hurt his back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.78,0:11:07.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but there's a hole in it \Neven though it's brand new.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.61,0:11:11.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering about that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:16.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it had a hole because it was old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.89,0:11:19.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And when I first looked at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.69,0:11:22.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the surface of the cushion \Nwas slightly damp.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.82,0:11:26.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There weren't any other \Nwet spots on the seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.91,0:11:28.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.82,0:11:31.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing strange about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.64,0:11:35.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was damp because Goto-san \Nspilled liquor on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:39.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And the cushion was defective, so \Na hole opened while he was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.06,0:11:42.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It made him lose his balance \Nand fall from his seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.01,0:11:44.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well?! You got a problem with that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.76,0:11:46.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, Mori-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.51,0:11:48.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This was definitely an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.88,0:11:50.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,An accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.51,0:11:51.98,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.98,0:11:57.53,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Using that, they could've made the \Nvictim fall, even from a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.19,0:12:02.77,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But without any evidence, this \Nwill be treated as an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.12,0:12:04.39,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.03,0:12:07.22,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Anything that would definitively \Nprove they did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.88,0:12:11.93,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.53,0:12:13.90,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.90,0:12:16.92,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means they must \Nstill have it on them...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:20.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The conclusive evidence the \Nculprit used in their trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.57,0:12:32.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably safe to assume \Nthere was no foul play.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.32,0:12:38.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. They seem to have motives, but \Nthose three couldn't have killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.05,0:12:39.21,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.01,0:12:42.86,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,How long do we have to wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.86,0:12:45.25,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.25,0:12:48.08,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,We have people we need to call.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:50.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.32,0:12:53.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After reviewing the crime scene, \Nall uncertainties have been—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.73,0:13:07.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's become clear to me that this is a \Nmurder made to look like an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.29,0:13:13.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Goto-san didn't accidentally \Nfall from his seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.96,0:13:16.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He was made to fall by the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.85,0:13:21.75,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you just say none of \Nthem could have killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.25,0:13:26.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,At first, that's what I believed, but \Nafter examining the inside of the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.74,0:13:30.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I realized the trick the culprit used.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.25,0:13:32.31,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.31,0:13:36.09,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,You think one of us killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.09,0:13:38.53,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,We were together the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.53,0:13:41.50,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't have killed the professor, \Nwho was sleeping in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.50,0:13:43.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's not impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.82,0:13:46.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All they needed to do was \Nslip the phone with the strap
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.25,0:13:52.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,through the gap between the headrest \Nand seat towards the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.04,0:13:54.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.71,0:13:58.15,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't it a coincidence that \NGoto-san fell from his seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.15,0:14:04.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit set up what you might call \Na timing device that caused Goto-san
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.41,0:14:08.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,to automatically fall from his seat \Neven if no one else was present
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.71,0:14:13.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,using the rubber air cushion and dry ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.77,0:14:17.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Dry ice sublimates from a \Nsolid directly into a gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.26,0:14:20.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,causing its volume to expand \Nby a factor of 800.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.97,0:14:27.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit packed said dry ice inside \Nthe air cushion and hid it on the seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.14,0:14:31.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,As time passed, the cushion \Nbegan to expand like a balloon
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:35.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,to a size large enough to cause \NGoto-san to fall from his seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.01,0:14:40.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The cushion was damp because the \Nlow temperature of the dry ice
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.26,0:14:43.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,cooled the moisture in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.28,0:14:45.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,causing it to condense on its surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.27,0:14:50.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The cushion continued to \Nexpand after Goto-san fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.67,0:14:54.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and once it could no longer \Ncontain the gas, it burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.67,0:15:00.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, they experimented many times to \Ndetermine the exact amount they should use,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.42,0:15:04.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so it would all have turned to gas \Nby the time the body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.01,0:15:08.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That would certainly leave no evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.99,0:15:13.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't it difficult to transport dry ice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.39,0:15:17.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the culprit used a certain \Npiece of outdoor equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.40,0:15:21.97,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! A cooler!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.97,0:15:22.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.41,0:15:27.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Using a cooler allowed the culprit to \Npreserve the dry ice until they needed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.60,0:15:30.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.01,0:15:35.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The individual with the cooler \Nwho used this trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.80,0:15:36.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Komada-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.15,0:15:43.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You created an excuse to remain in the \Ncar and passed the open phone with strap
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.51,0:15:48.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,through the gap beneath the \Nheadrest towards the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.42,0:15:55.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then you draped a blanket over Goto-san's \Nlegs in order to hide the dry ice-filled cushion,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.22,0:15:59.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and went shopping as though \Nnothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.78,0:16:02.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you calculated how \Nlarge the cushion would expand,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.27,0:16:05.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and how long it would take to \Nburst and bought one accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.55,0:16:08.75,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.75,0:16:12.03,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you don't think I did it just \Nbecause I approached the professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.74,0:16:18.52,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,And you said I passed the professor's phone \Nthough the gap and over the back of his seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.52,0:16:23.54,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten that the \Nprofessor called Saeki-senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.54,0:16:27.61,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,If his phone were back there, \Nhe couldn't have called anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.61,0:16:33.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I never said it was the professor's \Nphone that was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.31,0:16:35.45,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What are you—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.45,0:16:39.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying you're the one \Nwho called Saeki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.80,0:16:45.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You swapped out your phone for Goto-san's \Nand used it to fabricate your alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.87,0:16:52.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the phone attached to the \Nstrap that strangled Goto-san was yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.63,0:16:58.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you behaved strangely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.07,0:17:04.58,DCMain,KOOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Conan told me that when you saw \NSaeki-san return to the van,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.58,0:17:09.71,DCMain,KOOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you returned to the car while carrying \Nheavy bags full of groceries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.72,0:17:16.22,DCItalic,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we're leaving soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.22,0:17:17.71,DCItalic,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,We should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.71,0:17:19.21,DCItalic,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.21,0:17:21.99,DCItalic,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, I'm putting some bags in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.99,0:17:23.77,DCItalic,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.77,0:17:25.94,DCItalic,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking about \Nbringing the car around—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:26.72,DCItalic,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.50,0:17:33.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inoue-san, you were with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.05,0:17:35.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you wonder why he didn't \Nhave Saeki-san bring the car
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.58,0:17:39.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,in front of the store instead \Nof carrying so many heavy bags?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.88,0:17:41.79,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.79,0:17:46.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But, Komada-san, you went out \Nof your way to carry the bags.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.35,0:17:48.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:51.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's one reason you returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.79,0:17:54.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you needed to discover \NGoto-san's body with someone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.53,0:17:56.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,approach the body first,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:18:01.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and swap out your phone, which \Nyou used for the murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.11,0:18:05.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,for Goto-san's, which you used \Nto fabricate your alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.19,0:18:10.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,As the only other person with \Na flip phone like Goto-san's,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.52,0:18:12.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,only you could've used this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.36,0:18:15.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanted to save Goto-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.25,0:18:19.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you simply needed to pass the \Nstuck phone through the gap.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.34,0:18:24.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I knew something was off when you \Ndeliberately removed the phone from the strap.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.95,0:18:28.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You probably planned to reattach it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.41,0:18:34.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but you gave up on the idea when Conan and \NI entered the car unexpectedly quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.57,0:18:38.25,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,You're making this all up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.25,0:18:42.17,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it was dry ice, there's \Nno evidence it was used!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.53,0:18:46.19,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm the culprit, show me the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.59,0:18:49.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I could say the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.07,0:18:50.23,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.23,0:18:53.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi, how did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.56,0:18:58.57,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't find the damage you \Ndescribed on Goto-san's phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.57,0:19:00.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Damage?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.78,0:19:05.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And aren't these pieces of plastic?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.07,0:19:09.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they were stuck to the blanket.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.92,0:19:14.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When Goto-san fell, the \Nphone dangling over the back
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.71,0:19:17.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,struck a metal piece of the seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.41,0:19:20.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The shock sent those pieces \Nof plastic flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.30,0:19:26.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Komada-san, using an old \Nphone came back to bite you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.60,0:19:36.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,As we just heard in \NDetective Takagi's report,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.09,0:19:40.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Goto-san's phone was not damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.57,0:19:45.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means a different phone \Nwas used in the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.89,0:19:48.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You have that phone on you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.59,0:19:52.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,One with dents that should \Nmatch those pieces of plastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.34,0:19:54.36,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.82,0:20:06.15,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,Komada, why would you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.81,0:20:08.05,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.17,0:20:11.97,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,You probably had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.40,0:20:14.73,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,The professor's paper that won the award...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.20,0:20:17.16,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,It was originally my thesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.16,0:20:20.89,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,The professor stole my research topic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.28,0:20:23.17,DCMain,HARUKA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.62,0:20:26.22,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, the professor threatened me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.68,0:20:32.08,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,He told me to keep my mouth shut if I wanted \Nto keep doing research at the university.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.08,0:20:35.62,DCMain,SAEKI,0000,0000,0000,,You should've told someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.62,0:20:37.77,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,I had a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.77,0:20:40.83,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Since I was a child, I dreamed \Nof becoming a researcher!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.29,0:20:44.46,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,But... But that man...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.96,0:20:46.84,DCItalic,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, this isn't what you promised!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.53,0:20:50.10,DCItalic,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't I go to grad school?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.04,0:20:52.51,DCItalic,GOTOO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.51,0:20:56.52,DCItalic,GOTOO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you get a job at some company.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.96,0:20:58.95,DCItalic,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,A-A job?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.95,0:21:02.71,DCItalic,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I can't stay here, can't I at \Nleast go to a lab at another university?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.19,0:21:04.92,DCItalic,GOTO,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.92,0:21:07.27,DCItalic,GOTO,0000,0000,0000,,I have a lot of influence in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.27,0:21:10.45,DCItalic,GOTO,0000,0000,0000,,I can change your future with a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.68,0:21:15.61,DCItalic,GOTO,0000,0000,0000,,You were never meant for research.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.61,0:21:17.70,DCItalic,GOTO,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.12,0:21:21.70,DCItalic,GOTO,0000,0000,0000,,It really is a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.82,0:21:30.47,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,I ignored my research to repeatedly \Nexperiment and perfect this method.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.89,0:21:33.53,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,I was pretty confident it would work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.25,0:21:36.59,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,But I messed it up in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.59,0:21:40.58,DCMain,KOMADA,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I wasn't a good enough \Nresearcher after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.98,0:23:09.34,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you didn't know where we were going, \Nyou should've followed the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.34,0:23:12.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We came this way on the way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.69,0:23:17.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not doing something as pathetic \Nas asking the police for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.25,0:23:19.41,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But we're lost now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.41,0:23:22.12,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,We even have a GPS! How \Ndoes this even happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.49,0:23:25.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's giving we weird directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.40,0:23:26.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.27,0:23:29.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We made it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.53,0:23:32.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I knew my instincts were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.43,0:23:34.01,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.01,0:23:37.02,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't we just here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.53,0:23:40.74,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We won't be getting home for a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.31,0:23:48.61,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry. Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.74,0:23:51.74,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.84,0:23:54.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Inspector Megure?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.87,0:23:59.30,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What? You're staking out \Na counterfeiting operation?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.84,0:24:02.29,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's money!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.67,0:24:05.16,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,You violated the contract, signore.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.16,0:24:09.04,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you return all the notes you took?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Disappearing Detective Boys
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.72,0:24:13.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"The Disappearing Detective Boys!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Glazed Rice Dumplings
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.75,0:24:32.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.88,0:24:34.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Glazed rice dumplings!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.98,0:24:36.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}We're finally home.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.51,0:24:38.09,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Thanks for driving...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.09,0:24:39.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But it's the next day.
